<definition id="fs-idm107098976"><term>Echinodermata</term> <meaning id="fs-idp80776640">phylum of deuterostomes with spiny skin; exclusively marine organisms</meaning></definition>
<definition id="fs-idp134641584"><term>enterocoelom</term> <meaning id="fs-idp114963760">coelom formed by fusion of coelomic pouches budded from the endodermal lining of the archenteron</meaning></definition>
<definition id="fs-idp205635280"><term>madreporite</term> <meaning id="fs-idp55645184">pore for regulating entry and exit of water into the water vascular system</meaning></definition>
